oaOut(25.10)                                                      oaOut(25.10)

Name
       oaOut  - Saves floorplan, placement, and routing data in the OpenAccess
       format

Syntax
       oaOut

       [-help]

       <lib>

       <cell>

       <view>

       [-autoRemaster]

       [-copyTechFromReflib]

       [-cutRows]

       [-early_global_route]

       [-leafViewNames {<lefView1 lefView2 ...>}]

       [-noConnectivity [-noStdCells]]

       [-noOverwriteAbstract]

       [-refLibs {<refLib1 refLib2 ...>}]

       Saves floorplan, placement, and routing data in the OpenAccess format.

       You can use the oaOut command after importing the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each oaOut parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man oaOut.

       <lib>  Specifies the target OpenAccess library name.

       <cell> Specifies the target cell name.

       <view> Specifies the target view name.

       -autoRemaster
              Overrides  the reference libraries and leaf view names specified
              binding, and utilizes the cell layout viewing binding stored  on
              the  library  cell  master for each leaf cell (stored in the li-
              brary cell's layout library and layout view attributes).

              The binding can be specified using the set_cell_binding command.

       -copyTechFromReflib
              Copies the technology file to the current design library.

              Default: If you do not specify this parameter, Innovus  attaches
              the technology to the current design library.

              Note: This parameter applies only when you create libraries.

       -cutRows
              Specifies  that  rows are cut against placement obstructions and
              block halos, similar to the behavior of the defOut command.

              Default: Does not cut rows.

       -early_global_route
              Writes out a design containing Early Global Route data.

       -leafViewNames <{lefView1 lefView2> ...}
              Specifies a list of view names to be searched during  leaf  cell
              instance binding.

       -noConnectivity
              This  option  should  be used if the OpenAccess layout cellviews
              that are  being  used  in  remastering  (-autoRemaster  or  -re-
              fLibs/-leafViewNames)  do not have any terminals (as is the case
              when the layout cellview is created from GDSII/Stream data),  in
              which  case it is not possible to maintain netlist connectivity.
              Writes out a design that contains instances and physical shapes.
              When specified, the software creates an OpenAccess module domain
              using the instance hierarchy, but does not attempt to create any
              nets, pins, or instance pins.  Designs  written  out  using  the
              -noConnectivity  parameter  cannot  be reloaded into the Innovus
              software.

       -noOverwriteAbstract
              Prevents the software from overwriting abstracts  of  partitions
              and blackboxes.

              Default:  Innovus  overwrites abstracts of partitions and black-
              boxes. Innovus never overwrites abstracts of library data.

       -noStdCells
              Does not save instances of core cells to  the  OpenAccess  data-
              base.  However, if an instance is either fixed or covered, it is
              saved to the database.

              Use this parameter if you just need the preliminary  design  for
              DRC  checks  of  the  floorplan.  In such cases, leaving out the
              standard cell information makes the file smaller and reduces the
              DRC run time.

              Note: The -noStdCells parameter must be used with the -noConnec-
              tivity parameter.

       -refLibs {<refLib1 refLib2 ...>}
              Specifies the names of the external libraries that will  contain
              the  leaf  cell masters, LEF abstract, and technology file. This
              parameter only accepts library names, not paths. The mapping be-
              tween the external library name and its path is defined  in  the
              cds.lib  file.  Innovus  references  technology information only
              from the first library in the list of libraries.

Example
              * The following command shows the usage of ITDB style libraries:

                createLib myDesignLib -referenceTech {techLib}

                oaOut -autoRemaster myDesignLib myTopCell layout

